<div class="pageContent pageText">
  <div class="text">
    <h3>Opportunity</h3>
    <p class="lead">
      Weedmaps is one of the best places to go to talk about cannabis. Thousands of people everyday to to Weedmaps to post pics of strains they grow; patients ask questions for experts; folks looking for the best dispensaries around; others providing impromptu reviews of products they just bought. Other users comment and a lively conversation ensues.
    </p>
    <p>
      This community has been growing organically over the last eight or nine years. The company hasn’t put to much thought into it as other initiatives take priority.
    </p>
    <p>
      But my team saw things differently. We see incredibly unique behaviors that don’t happen elsewhere on the internet. We see wake-and-bake ceremonies, greetings to new members, users saying hello to each other. It’s a genuinely nice online community. We wanted to take it to the next level.
    </p>
    <p>
      We see Weedmaps Social as a driver of the advertising and commerce components of the business. Weedmaps lets users search and find storefronts, doctors, products, and brands as well as place orders for delivery, pick-up, and mail order in some areas.
    </p>
  </div>

</div>
